<item>
            <title>[SPR-347] inconsistent behavior between DefaultLobHandler and OracleLobHandler</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-347</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I found the getBlobAsBinaryStream() of the DefaultLobHandler doesn&apos;t match the behavior of the getBlobAsBinaryStream() of OracleLobHandler when comes to processing the NULL column. The former one will return a 0 byte stream while the latter one will return null value (because it uses jdbc&apos;s getstream). I think the DefaultLobHandler should also return a 0 byte stream, as following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	public InputStream getBlobAsBinaryStream(ResultSet rs, int columnIndex) throws SQLException &lt;/p&gt;
{
		logger.debug(&quot;Returning BLOB as binary stream&quot;);
		InputStream is = rs.getBinaryStream(columnIndex);
		return is != null? is:new ByteArrayInputStream(new byte[0]));
	}</description>
            <key id="10580">SPR-347</key>
            <summary>inconsistent behavior between DefaultLobHandler and OracleLobHandler</summary>
