                            <comment id="11089" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Fri, 24 Sep 2004 05:02:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, this was not clearly specified before; it was just hinted at that it&apos;s supposed to follow ResultSet.getBytes and co. IMO, the correct behavior is to return Java null for SQL NULL, following the JDBC spec here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I&apos;ve just fixed OracleLobHandler rather than DefaultLobHandler, to consistently make all LobHandler getters return null in case of SQL NULL. Hopefully noone is relying on the old behavior; OTOH, this couldn&apos;t have worked with DefaultLobHandler anyway.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
